{{Lunisolar March}} '''March 4''' is the 4th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * [[天喜]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1053]] {{ill|March 26|ja|3月26日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The great Amitābha Hall (鳳凰堂) at Heidōin (平等院) in Uji was completed under the direction of Fujiwara Yorimichi. * [[Meiwa]] 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1771]] {{ill|April 18|ja|4月18日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Sugita Genpaku and Maeno Ryōtaku observed the dissection of condemned prisoners; the very next day they began translating the work “Tahel Anatomia.” * [[Tenmei]] 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1788]] {{ill|April 9|ja|4月9日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Tokugawa Iezawa appointed Matsudaira Sadatoki as his shōgun’s assistant (補佐), marking the beginning of the Kansei reforms. * [[嘉慶 (中国)|嘉慶]] 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1796]] {{ill|April 11|ja|4月11日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – In the Qing dynasty, a rebellion was triggered by a group of Bai Lian (White Lotus) adherents—peasant groups forming a Maitreya-based religious association. * [[Bunka]] 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1806]] {{ill|April 22|ja|4月22日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – A great fire, known as the “Great Cultural Fire,” broke out in Edo. * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1837]] {{ill|April 8|ja|4月8日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Due to the Great Tenpō Famine, the Tokugawa shogunate established rice relief granaries throughout Edo. * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1863]] {{ill|April 21|ja|4月21日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Tokugawa Iemochi entered Nijō Castle in Kyoto, the first time in 230 years since Shōkō had reigned. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1868]] {{ill|April 1|ja|4月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – At Sunpu Castle, Tetsusaburō Yamaoka met with Saigō Takamori, appealing with a spirit of submission to save the Tokugawa family. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1872]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The soldiers safeguarding the emperor—10,000 strong from the Satsuma, Chōshū, and Tosa domains—were re-designated as the Konoei.
== Births == * {{ill|Genroku|ja|元禄|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 10th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1697]] {{ill|April 24|ja|4月24日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Kamo Mafuchi, a Kokugaku scholar (<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mabuchi-kinenkan.jp/history/index.html|title=賀茂真淵について|publisher=賀茂真淵記念館|accessdate=2021-05-03}}</ref>) (died [[1769]]). == Deaths ==
