== Events == * [[天喜]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1053]] [[:en:March 26|March 26]]) – The great Amitābha Hall (鳳凰堂) at Heidōin (平等院) in Uji was completed under the direction of Fujiwara Yorimichi. * [[Meiwa]] 8th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1771]] [[:en:April 18|April 18]]) – Sugita Genpaku and Maeno Ryōtaku observed the dissection of condemned prisoners; the very next day they began translating the work “Tahel Anatomia.” * [[Tenmei]] 8th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1788]] [[:en:April 9|April 9]]) – Tokugawa Iezawa appointed Matsudaira Sadatoki as his shōgun’s assistant (補佐), marking the beginning of the Kansei reforms. * [[嘉慶 (中国)|嘉慶]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1796]] [[:en:April 11|April 11]]) – In the Qing dynasty, a rebellion was triggered by a group of Bai Lian (White Lotus) adherents—peasant groups forming a Maitreya-based religious association. * [[Bunka]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1806]] [[:en:April 22|April 22]]) – A great fire, known as the “Great Cultural Fire,” broke out in Edo. * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 8th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1837]] [[:en:April 8|April 8]]) – Due to the Great Tenpō Famine, the Tokugawa shogunate established rice relief granaries throughout Edo. * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1863]] [[:en:April 21|April 21]]) – Tokugawa Iemochi entered Nijō Castle in Kyoto, the first time in 230 years since Shōkō had reigned. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1868]] [[:en:April 1|April 1]]) – At Sunpu Castle, Tetsusaburō Yamaoka met with Saigō Takamori, appealing with a spirit of submission to save the Tokugawa family. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1872]] [[:en:April 16|April 16]]) – The soldiers safeguarding the emperor—10,000 strong from the Satsuma, Chōshū, and Tosa domains—were re-designated as the Konoei.
== Births == * [[:en:Genroku|Genroku]] 10th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1697]] [[:en:April 24|April 24]]) – Kamo Mafuchi, a Kokugaku scholar (<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mabuchi-kinenkan.jp/history/index.html|title=賀茂真淵について|publisher=賀茂真淵記念館|accessdate=2021-05-03|qq=}}</ref>) (died [[1769]]). == Deaths ==
